across different genes and organisms.<\/p>\n\n<p>Note as well that the whole notion of recessive and dominant traits is probably an over-simplification and, in fact, there are subtle differences between homozygotes and heterozygotes in many, perhaps most, cases so I'm not sure how useful an estimate would be even if you had one.<\/p>\n","answer_id":16254,"question_id":16250,"up_vote_count":3}],"link":"http://biology.stackexchange.com/questions/16250/dominance-recessivity-of-new-mutations","last_activity_date":1396270763,"creation_date":1396262711,"answer_count":1,"title":"Dominance/recessivity of new mutations","body":"<p><strong>What is the distribution/probability density function (<a href=\"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Probability_density_function\" rel=\"nofollow\">PDF<\/a>) of recessivity/dominance of new mutations?<\/strong><\/p>\n\n<hr>\n\n<p>I very welcome any partial answer that does not give the whole PDF but just some information about the expected value or the variance of this distribution.<\/p>\n\n<p><a href=\"http://biology.stackexchange.com/questions/16251/effect-on-fitness-of-mutations\">Here<\/a> is a related question<\/p>\n","question_id":16250,"tags":["evolution","natural-selection","mutations","population-dynamics","population-biology"],"score":1,"accepted_answer_id":16254,"down_vote_count":0,"is_answered":true,"view_count":42,"up_vote_count":1},{"owner":{"user_type":"does_not_exist","display_name":"user6116"},"answers":[{"owner":{"profile_image":"https://www.gravatar.com/avatar/da1e8af33e12bfa60ea44b3af00c0d03?s=128&d=identicon&r=PG&f=1","user_type":"moderator","user_id":5144,"link":"http://biology.stackexchange.com/users/5144/chris","reputation":31001,"display_name":"Chris"},"score":2,"is_accepted":true,"comments":[{"owner":{"profile_image":"https://i.stack.imgur.com/RIrIa.jpg?s=128&g=1","user_type":"registered","user_id":5922,"link":"http://biology.stackexchange.com/users/5922/playsdice","reputation":646,"display_name":"PlaysDice"},"score":0,"