t disease (angina) which causes pain in the jaw and arm. Perhaps even more interestingly, if a nerve is cut and then grows back linking to the wrong nerve it may lead to the completely wrong part of the body being identified when touched. Also if the brain itself is stimulated in these corresponding areas, a person will feel he or she is indeed being touched in a certain part of the body. <\/p>\n","answer_id":16243,"question_id":16224,"up_vote_count":3}],"link":"http://biology.stackexchange.com/questions/16224/nervous-system-nerve-signals","last_activity_date":1396222903,"creation_date":1396201352,"answer_count":1,"title":"Nervous system : Nerve signals","body":"<p>If the electrical signals from all the various organs throughout the body eventually connect to the nerves in the spinal column traveling up to the brain, how does the brain differentiate the different signals.  Is the nerve in the spinal column like an electrical conduit with many wires inside?<\/p>\n","question_id":16224,"tags":["neuroscience"],"score":2,"accepted_answer_id":16243,"down_vote_count":0,"closed_reason":"duplicate","is_answered":true,"view_count":43,"up_vote_count":2},{"owner":{"user_type":"does_not_exist","display_name":"user6116"},"comments":[{"owner":{"profile_image":"https://i.stack.imgur.com/EJDAE.jpg?s=128&g=1","user_type":"registered","user_id":5694,"link":"http://biology.stackexchange.com/users/5694/v-ix","reputation":607,"display_name":"V_ix"},"score":0,"post_id":16222,"edited":false,"creation_date":1396223659,"comment_id":21859,"body":"This question is way too generic as it stands. I suggest asking about a specific situation as an example."}],"answers":[{"owner":{"profile_image":"https://www.gravatar.com/avatar/53c30bc1f1ac4e6b256e52b62124da86?s=128&d=identicon&r=PG","user_type":"registered","user_id":1757,"link":"http://biology.stackexchange.com/users/1757/androidpenguin","reputation":4652,"display_name":"AndroidPenguin","accept_rate":25},"score":1,"is_accepted":true,"down_vote_c