fter touching the gecko, keep it away from food preparation areas and don't put the lizard in your mouth, you should be fine.<\/p>\n\n<p>If you're talking about geckos living free in your home, as is common in many tropical places, I have never heard of any health risks associated with them. If anything, I would think that the geckos would <em>reduce<\/em> health risks by eating insects such as cockroaches and mosquitoes that are prominent disease carriers.<\/p>\n","answer_id":8503,"question_id":8497,"up_vote_count":2}],"link":"http://biology.stackexchange.com/questions/8497/how-do-pet-gecko-lizards-pose-a-health-risk","last_activity_date":1395929178,"creation_date":1369364159,"answer_count":1,"title":"How do pet gecko lizards pose a health risk?","body":"<p>Does having gecko lizards living in your house pose any health risk?<\/p>\n","question_id":8497,"tags":["zoology","pathology","herpetology"],"score":2,"accepted_answer_id":8503,"down_vote_count":0,"is_answered":true,"view_count":554,"up_vote_count":2,"last_edit_date":1395929178},{"owner":{"profile_image":"https://i.stack.imgur.com/f0PGT.jpg?s=128&g=1","user_type":"registered","user_id":3615,"link":"http://biology.stackexchange.com/users/3615/biogirl","reputation":3923,"display_name":"biogirl","accept_rate":89},"answers":[{"owner":{"profile_image":"https://www.gravatar.com/avatar/da1e8af33e12bfa60ea44b3af00c0d03?s=128&d=identicon&r=PG&f=1","user_type":"moderator","user_id":5144,"link":"http://biology.stackexchange.com/users/5144/chris","reputation":31001,"display_name":"Chris"},"score":2,"is_accepted":true,"comments":[{"owner":{"profile_image":"https://i.stack.imgur.com/SjvUL.png?s=128&g=1","user_type":"moderator","user_id":3340,"link":"http://biology.stackexchange.com/users/3340/wysiwyg","reputation":23153,"display_name":"WYSIWYG","accept_rate":80},"score":0,"post_id":16095,"edited":false,"creation_date":1395841044,"comment_id":21611,"body":"Small addition: Isopropanol having a bigger alkyl group makes the solution more organic in nature compared to ethanol. Why isopropanol and not n-propanol is perhaps because it is easy to manufacture isopropanol. n-propanol is better at precipitating smaller nucleic acids."},{"owner":{"profile_image":"https://www.gravatar.com/avatar/da1e8af33e12bfa60ea44b3af00c0d03?s=128&d=identicon&r=PG&f=1","user_type":"moderator","user_id":5144,"link":"http://biology.stackexchange.com/users/5144/chris","reputation":31001,"display_name":"Chris"},"score":0,"post_id":16095,"reply_to_user":{"profile_image":"https://i.stack.imgur.com/SjvUL.png?s=128&g=1","user_type":"moderator","user_id":3340,"link":"http://biology.stackexchange.com/users/3340/wysiwyg","reputation":23153,"display_name":"WYSIWYG","accept_rate":80},"edited":false,"creation_date":1395852429,"comment_id":21627,"body":"It is because isopropanol is less toxic in the handling than n-propanol. n-propanol can cause severe eye damage and is generally more toxic than ethanol or isopropanol."},{"owner":{"profile_image":"https://i.stack.imgur.com/SjvUL.png?s=128&g=1","user_type":"moderator","user_id":3340,"link":"http://biology.stackexchange.com/users/3340/wysiwyg","reputation":23153,"display_name":"WYSIWYG","accept_rate":80},"score":0,"post_id":16095,"edited":false,"creation_date":1395893651,"comment_id":21699,"body":"Point taken. but it is also easy to manufasture isopropanol :P"},{"owner":{"user_type":"does_not_exist","display_name":"user560"},"score":0,"post_id":16095,"edited":false,"creation_date":1395927081,"comment_id":21722,"body":"Not to mention every molecular bio lab has isopropanol on hand."},{"owner":{"profile_image":"https://i.stack.imgur.com/SjvUL.png?s=128&g=1","user_type":"moderator","user_id":3340,"link":"http://biology.stackexchange.com/users/3340/wysiwyg","reputation":23153,"display_name":"WYSIWYG","accept_rate":80},"score":0,"post_id":16095,"edited":false,"creation_date":1395928008,"comment_id":21725,"body":"@Chris.. I am not sure why you say n-propanol is more toxic. It can be ea